description:
Implement error messages that match Node.js exactly for test parity.

**Error messages (must match exactly):**
- `"Error: No JSONL files found in {path}"` (for --data-dir with no files)
- `"Error: No Claude Code data found for {path}"` (for project path)
- `"Error: No Claude Code sessions found"` (for all projects scan)

**Implementation pattern:**
```zig
pub fn main() !void {
    run() catch |err| {
        // Zig 0.15.2: Use std.debug.print for stderr
        switch (err) {
            error.NoJsonlFiles => std.debug.print("Error: No JSONL files found in {s}\\n", .{path}),
            error.NoSessions => std.debug.print("Error: No Claude Code sessions found\\n", .{}),
            // etc.
        }
        std.process.exit(1);
    };
}
```

**Exit codes:**
- 0 for success
- 1 for errors

**Reference:** bin/cc-query.js lines 84-96

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Error messages match Node exactly (case, punctuation, spacing)
- Exit code 1 on error
- Error output goes to stderr
